        public void add(Object entity,
       String idPropertyName)
         throws SerializationException,
                DeserializationException
        Adds the entity to the default graph of the KB. If an entity with the same property idPropertyName already exists in the default graph, the old entity will be overwritten.
        Parameters:
        entity - the entity to be persisted
        idPropertyName - the parameter name identifying the unique identifier of the entity
        Throws:
        SerializationException
        DeserializationException

      • add

        public void add(Object entity,
       String idPropertyName,
       String graphName)
         throws SerializationException,
                DeserializationException
        Adds the entity to a specific graph in the KB. If an entity with the same property idPropertyName already exists in the graph, the old entity will be overwritten.
        Parameters:
        entity - the entity to be persisted
        idPropertyName - the parameter name identifying the unique identifier of the entity
        graphName - the name of the graph where the entity should be persisted
        Throws:
        SerializationException
        DeserializationException
